        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: BERLIN to PRAGUE by train from €18.99 | 2026 timetable & tickets\nurl: \"https://www.seat61.com/trains-and-routes/berlin-to-prague-by-train.htm\"\ndescription: \"Comfortable air-conditioned ComfortJet trains with restaurant car & free WiFi link Berlin and Prague every two hours, 388 km (241 miles) in under 4 hours, centre to centre with great scenery along the scenic Elbe & Vlatava rivers. In 2026, all departures use new Czech Railways ComfortJet carriages.\"\npage_age: \"\"\nprofile_name: Seat61\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/o9MdoxbMYXvNs6KaXrQivgSAYZQGqlBBQHdZQCkVO-8/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvZjA2YTUzOTcx/MGY5OTg1MjhjMjQ3/YjIwMTgxNDlkNzE3/YTFiNTk4N2Q1NDJk/YzE0ZDIwNjczM2Yz/MDNkYjY4OC93d3cu/c2VhdDYxLmNvbS8\"\nthumbnail: null\nextra_snippets: \"Train travel in America... ... Comments? Feedback? Need help? Email the Man in Seat Sixty-One! ... Thank you for visiting... Comfortable air-conditioned ComfortJet trains with restaurant car & free WiFi link Berlin and Prague every two hours, 388 km (241 miles) in under 4 hours, centre to centre with great scenery along the scenic Elbe & Vlatava rivers. In 2026, all departures use new Czech Railways ComfortJet carriages.|CJH = Hungaria, modern Czech Railways ComfortJet train with 1st & 2nd class and restaurant car to/from Budapest. Times may vary, check times for your date of travel at int.bahn.de. Due to trackwork, on Mondays from 16 March to 12 December 2026 all Berlin-Prague trains are cancelled except the 17:28 & 19:28 from Berlin & 06:31 from Prague.|Left luggage lockers in Berlin & Prague - General advice & tips for European train travel.|Berlin to Prague by train is 388 km or 241 miles. Advance-purchase fares start at €18.99 in 2nd class or €29.99 in 1st class. Sparpreis (savings) fares are advance-purchase fares with dynamic prices & limited availability at each price level. They are only good for the specific departure you book, limited refunds, no changes to travel plans. A round trip is two one-ways. If you're happy to book ahead and commit to a specific train, this is what you want.\"\nhash: 22e1313858c34b5c\nembed_ref: seat61.com-ALR\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
