        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: Prague to Berlin - 13 Best Ways to Travel in 2026\nurl: \"https://www.sidetriptours.com/travel-info/prague-to-berlin/\"\ndescription: \"... The train is the most popular way to travel from Prague to Berlin, and it is easy to see why. Six EuroCity services run daily, with departures from Prague every two hours between 6:25 AM and 4:25 PM.\"\npage_age: \"February 11, 2026\"\nprofile_name: Sidetrip Tours\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/1p1lLiD0yqMDoXvYfmFJS6GK7PZFG1m8yD0NLaOonxQ/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMDM3MDVkNjUw/ZDBkYWEyMWI1NWVk/YmMxMzVlYWIxNGRk/MDUwY2M1ZWU0NjQ0/YTU4MmJkNzAyN2Y0/MjQ2MGUzYy93d3cu/c2lkZXRyaXB0b3Vy/cy5jb20v\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/vZWdCh-BTrfPpfLq72vVtpI6qUAhWBxr5KtrwSBXkII/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9zaWRl/dHJpcC1wcm9kdWN0/aW9uLW1lZGlhLnMz/LmFtYXpvbmF3cy5j/b20vYmxvZ19pbWFn/ZXMvUHJhZ3VlLUJl/cmxpbjJ4LmpwZw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://sidetrip-production-media.s3.amazonaws.com/blog_images/Prague-Berlin2x.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"While Prague draws visitors with its castles and cobblestones, Berlin captivates with museums, street art, and contemporary culture. Thankfully, the route between them is easy to navigate, with several convenient travel options. Trains and buses run multiple times daily, but for travelers looking to make the transit day more special, a sightseeing transfer tour allows stops in Dresden, Moritzburg, and the Saxon Switzerland region, turning the trip into a mini-adventure.|In this guide, we'll walk you through the best ways to travel from Prague to Berlin, with updated travel times, price ranges, and key route details. ... The train is the most popular way to travel from Prague to Berlin, and it is easy to see why. Six EuroCity services run daily, with departures from Prague every two hours between 6:25 AM and 4:25 PM.|Sit on the left side of the train facing the direction of travel for the best views of the sandstone cliffs and forested gorges as you cross into Germany. ... Berlin rewards patience. The more you understand about the city before you arrive, the more it gives back. The Prague to Berlin Transfer Tour uses your travel day to build exactly that.|Before you travel, look up the size and weight limits on the Flixbus and RegioJet websites, as these can differ. Book your Prague to Berlin bus on Flixbus | Book with RegioJet ... The train gets you there in four and a half hours, but it passes through some of the most dramatic scenery in Central Europe without a single stop.\"\nhash: e5da8e87da10d5f1\nembed_ref: sidetriptours.com-2Kb\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
